//body Squat: 15 reps * 3 sets. Targets quads, hamstrings, and glutes. Stand with feet apart, lower into a sitting position, then stand back up. Push-up: 10 reps * 3 sets. Works the chest, shoulders, and triceps. Keep your body straight and lower it to the ground using your arms. Lunges: 12 reps * 3 sets. Strengthens legs and glutes. Take a step forward, lower your hips until both knees are bent, then push back up. Plank: Hold for 30 seconds * 3 sets. Strengthens the core. With forearms on the ground, form a straight line from head to heels. Burpees: 8 reps * 3 sets. A full-body exercise. From standing, squat down, jump back into a plank, then jump back to squat and leap up. Jumping Jacks: 20 reps * 3 sets. A cardio exercise. Jump with legs and arms going outward and then return to the starting position. Mountain Climbers: 15 reps * 3 sets. Works the whole body. Start in a plank and alternate driving your knees towards your chest rapidly. High Knees: 20 reps * 3 sets. A cardio move. Run in place lifting your knees high at a comfortable pace. Deadlift: 12 reps * 3 sets. Targets the back, glutes, and legs. Lift a weight off the ground by hinging at the hips and standing up. Leg Raises: 12 reps * 3 sets. Strengthens the lower abdomen. Lie on your back, legs straight, and lift them to a 90-degree angle. Russian Twists: 15 reps * 3 sets. Work the abdomen. Sit with a slight lean back, lift feet if possible, and twist the torso side to side. Bicycle Crunches: 20 reps * 3 sets. Target abs and obliques. Lie on your back, hands behind your head, and alternate elbow to opposite knee. Pull-ups: 8 reps * 3 sets. Strengthen the upper body. Hang from a bar and pull yourself up until your chin is over the bar, then lower back down. Dumbbell Rows: 10 reps * 3 sets. Work the back and biceps. Bend over, one hand on a bench, and pull a weight up to your side. Bench Press: 12 reps * 3 sets. Works the chest, shoulders, and triceps. Lie on a bench and push a weight up from your chest until arms are straight. Shoulder Press: 10 reps * 3 sets. Strengthens shoulders and arms. Press weights overhead from shoulder height until arms are extended. Bicep Curls: 12 reps * 3 sets. Target the biceps. Curl weights from a hanging position up to your shoulders. Tricep Dips: 15 reps * 3 sets. Strengthen the triceps. Lower and raise your body with your arms on a bench or chair. Box Jumps: 10 reps * 3 sets. Improve leg power. Jump onto and off a sturdy box or platform with both feet. Wall Sit: Hold for 1 minute * 3 sets. Strengthens the legs and glutes. Sit against a wall in a squat position with legs at a 90-degree angle. Calf Raises: 15 reps * 3 sets. Strengthen the calves. Lift your heels off the ground and lower them back down. Hamstring Curls : 12 reps * 3 sets. Hamstring Curls target the back of your legs, improving flexibility and strength. Romanian Deadlift: 10 reps * 3 sets. Romanian Deadlift strengthens the lower back and hamstrings, focusing on the hinge movement. Side Plank: Hold for 30 seconds (each side) * 3 sets. Side Plank emphasizes core stability and strength, particularly along the sides of your abdomen. Flutter Kicks: 20 reps * 3 sets. Flutter Kicks are a core exercise focusing on the lower abdominals and hip flexors. Superman: Hold for 20 seconds * 3 sets. Superman exercise strengthens the back muscles and improves posture. Kettlebell Swings: 15 reps * 3 sets. Kettlebell Swings work the entire body, especially the posterior chain, for power and endurance. Russian Kettlebell Twist: 15 reps * 3 sets. Russian Kettlebell Twist targets obliques and abs for core rotation and strength. Skater Lunges: 12 reps (each side) * 3 sets. Skater Lunges increase lateral movement agility, leg strength, and balance. Burpee Box Jumps: 8 reps * 3 sets.Burpee Box Jumps combine explosive leg power and endurance, using a box to jump on and off.
